entries.meaning: (obsolete) A misshapen person; a misshapen body. [14th–17th c.]
A misshapen object; now especially, a broken item (especially food) sold individually at a cheaper price. [from 19th c.]
examples: Mis-shapes, mistakes, misfits  Raised on a diet of broken biscuits.

verbs.description: misshape (third-person singular simple present misshapes, present participle misshaping, simple past misshaped, past participle misshaped or (obsolete or poetic) misshapen)

entries.meaning: To shape badly or incorrectly. [from 15th c.]
examples: Major Rawls drove us to our motel  […]  where a swimming pool with underwater lights had the disturbing effect of substantially enlarging and misshaping the swimmers.
